<TITLE> DMCH suspends recruitment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 15 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka Medical College and Hospital temporarily suspended all staff appointment on Friday over allegations of favouritism. A high-powered three-member committee has also been formed, headed by a joint secretary of health and family welfare, said a government release. The decisions were made in an emergency meeting at health minister AFM Ruhal Haque's residence to "look into the circumstances that had arisen". Among others, prime minister's health adviser Dr Modasser Ali, additional secretary B D Mitra and Health Directorate director general professor Shah Manir Hossain were present at the meeting. The fourth-class employees of the country's premier public hoospital confined director Brigadier General Bazle Quader inside his office for two hours and a half on Jan 13 demanding cancellation of the ongoing staff recruitment. It was alleged that all the new employees were being recruited according to lists provided by the pro-Awami League doctors' forum Swadhinata Chikitsak Parisad and the Bangladesh Medical Association, which is also heavily influenced by the ruling party. bd
